body:
I have built export functionality using exceljs,its working fine in chrome,but its usage in firefox lets other pages in application break or they doesn't load on first click,it requires double click and modals doesnt load at all,they break completely and this happens in firefox,everything works fine in chrome.
Things I have tried to solve this:
1.added below polyfills suggested in npm module page
// polyfills required by exceljs
require('core-js/modules/es.promise'); // this caused issue like it was overriding zone.js promise and app was not loading so had to remove it
require('core-js/modules/es.string.includes');
require('core-js/modules/es.object.assign');
require('core-js/modules/es.object.keys');
require('core-js/modules/es.symbol');
require('core-js/modules/es.symbol.async-iterator');
require('regenerator-runtime/runtime');
2. Tried to install npm  regenerator-runtime and core-js
3.Tried downgrading exceljs 3.8.1 and @types/node 12.11.1. as per suggested by someone in exceljs issues link 
[https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/issues/810]
4.Added min.js through angular.json like "scripts": ["node_modules/exceljs/dist/exceljs.min.js"] [https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/issues/810](url)
5.Added import * as ExcelJS from 'exceljs/dist/exceljs.min.js' from the above link [https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/issues/810](url)

None of the above things solved my issue.It doesnt throw any error in console,the other pages in application just breaks and functionalities doesn't work

